<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LAWNDALE OUSTS 2ND CITY MANAGER IN 2 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lawndale City Manager James Arnold, who faces criminal misdemeanor charges in 
the demolition of three city buildings that contained asbestos, was ousted this 
week by a three-member majority of the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
Arnold is the second city manager to be fired by the council within two years. 
</P>
<P>
He described the agreement as amicable and said he has no hard feelings about 
the council's decision. "The city's been good to me," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Said Councilman William Johnson: "We just feel the city of Lawndale has been 
through a lot of problems and turmoil in the past, and we feel a change is 
needed." Council members who supported the ouster said the asbestos case was a 
factor but problems with the city's budget were a larger concern. 
</P>
