<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DRIVER DIES AFTER HE WAS SHOT NEAR FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist who was shot in the head while driving onto a freeway ramp in 
Sherman Oaks has died, Los Angeles police said Friday. There are no suspects in 
the case. 
</P>
<P>
Juan Manrique, 18, of Arleta died Thursday afternoon at the Medical Center of 
North Hollywood, a day after the shooting at the intersection of Woodman Avenue 
and the Ventura Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Manrique and a friend were about to turn onto the westbound on-ramp 
to the freeway when a car sped by them on Woodman and several shots were fired. 
Manrique was struck once in the head. His passenger, whose identity was not 
released, was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the motive for the shooting was not known but believe it could be 
gang-related because Manrique reportedly associated with gang members. 
</P>
