<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN WHO KILLED BABY SENTENCED TO 16 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A North Hollywood man who struck and killed a 2-year-old boy suffering from 
Down's syndrome was sentenced Friday to 16 years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
Anthony Michael Malone pleaded guilty last month to voluntary manslaughter 
after prosecutors agreed to drop a murder charge against him. 
</P>
<P>
He received the maximum sentence for manslaughter -- 11 years -- plus five 
years for a prior burglary conviction, said Deputy Dist. Atty. Jeffrey S. 
Gootman. 
</P>
<P>
The baby, Jonathan Moreno, died July 27, 1988, after he was struck by Malone, 
police said. The child was the son of Malone's 19-year-old girlfriend, Theresa 
Givens, who was at work when the child died. 
</P>
<P>
Gootman said prosecutors dropped the murder charge because they could not prove 
that Malone intended to kill the boy. 
</P>
