<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAX INCREASE: DEBATE OVER WHO WILL PAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am disturbed that our President and Congress can only think of increasing 
taxes as the solution to the deficit. They have treated our outrageous foreign 
aid as sacrosanct. 
</P>
<P>
Forty years-plus is long enough to support the world! Our seniors are of the 
generation that fought in World War II, rebuilt the world with their money, 
preserved the peace with their sons and daughters, and now the politicians are 
afraid they are too affluent and need to pay more taxes. None of the American 
people need to pay more taxes. We need relief from giving money away to 
countries which no longer need it and/or countries whose leaders line their 
pockets while their people suffer. 
</P>
<P>
