<P>
SMOKING BAN IN RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I'm sitting here reading your editorial wherein proponents of no smoking in Los 
Angeles city restaurants feel that the ban should cover a larger area, 
countywide, maybe statewide. I quote: ". . . People who smoke cigarettes or 
cigars or pipes inflict their dirty addiction on innocents who happen to be 
sharing their airspace." 
</P>
<P>
Airspace, well go figure! It's 100 degrees today, the sky is a putrid shade of 
gray-brown, the "airspace" smells foul, and all they can worry about is smoking 
in restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
I am also a nonsmoker; however, self-righteous and pompous I am not. Get real, 
Los Angeles. Stop blaming smokers for the damage Southern California and its 
inhabitants caused to the environment decades ago by sheer, self-centered 
greed. 
</P>
<P>
LYNNE NIELSEN 
