<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070790-0052 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 243894 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 7, 1990, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 2; Column 2; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
84 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO NASTY MARINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was relieved to hear that both the Navy and the Marines have banned sales of 
"As Nasty as They Wanna Be." 
</P>
<P>
I'm sure their reason for the ban was not censorship but rather to protect 
their tender recruits from hearing the foul language and sexually explicit 
material contained on this album. 
</P>
<P>
After all, when a sailor comes into port, illicit sex is the furthest thing 
from his mind. 
</P>
<P>
And any drill instructor can tell you how easily a Marine is offended by foul 
language. 
</P>
<P>
KEN CHASE 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne 
</P>
</TEXT>
