<P>
ROCKY FLATS SECURITY BREAKDOWN REVEALED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Energy Department announced that it has suspended handling of all plutonium 
at its Rocky Flats, Colo., nuclear weapons plant because of security 
breakdowns. 
</P>
<P>
Rocky Flats, which produces plutonium triggers for nuclear weapons, has had its 
manufacturing operations suspended since December because of safety and 
environmental problems. The latest order applies to all handling and movement 
of nuclear materials, the department said. The announcement, reported by the 
Washington Post in its Saturday editions, gave no details of the security 
breaches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
