<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oakland woman died after her car was struck by a police car that was 
traveling at an estimated 55 m.p.h. through an intersection during a high-speed 
chase, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Patricia Welsh, 41, failed to yield for the patrol car, which was 
using its siren and flashing lights while chasing a van whose passengers were 
suspected in an East Oakland shooting. Sgt. Earl Sargent said the officers 
"were in pursuit of people suspected of attempted murder. They were well within 
policy." Welsh's passenger, Joe Fernandez of Oakland, was hospitalized in 
serious condition. Two officers in the car received minor injuries. The van got 
away. 
