<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNTY OK OF RANCHLAND DEVELOPMENT RULED 
LEGAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Superior Court judge ruled Friday that Los Angeles County legally approved 
the Paramount Ranch development in Agoura, handing a stinging defeat to 
opponents who claimed the luxury 150-home development did not get an adequate 
environmental review. 
</P>
<P>
Under Judge David P. Yaffe's ruling, construction could start soon on the 
scenic, oak-studded tract where the Renaissance Pleasure Faire was formerly 
held. State and federal parks agencies had tried to buy the 320-acre site for 
the Santa Monica Mountains National Recreation Area. 
</P>
<P>
The Sierra Club, the Las Virgenes Homeowners Federation and Friends of the 
Santa Monica Mountains had contended that the county rubber-stamped an 
environmental impact report prepared by developers' consultants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
